## Thoughts / synthesis

- **Opportunity is less “build app with AI” and more “prevent AI-made app disasters.”**
- Teams are moving fast with generated backends and skipping security review; this creates immediate pain and budget.
- There is a second-order opportunity in **agent usability economics**:
  - “Can my repo fit in context?”
  - “How much does this architecture cost in tokens?”
  - “Can the agent debug prod issues quickly from logs?”
- There’s room for a creator angle too: people crave blunt, practical takes on what fails in real deployments (not hype threads).

